 The Impact of AI Features on Android App Permissions: GitHub-Ready Tables and Chart Text

> Data source: `CI research data2.xlsx`.  
> In this study, every `1/0` value indicates whether a permission is declared in the Android manifest:  
> `1 = declared / present`, `0 = absent`.  
> This does **not** directly prove that the user granted the permission, nor does it prove that the app actually used the permission at runtime.

> Research scope: This study examines the relationship between **AI features, recommendation systems, multimodal input, advertising personalization, identity/social graph access, behavioral monitoring, background service capabilities**, and Android permission structures.

