## 1. Codebook: AI-relevant Permission Categories

### 1.1 Core analytical categories

| Category | Definition | Example permissions | Why it matters | Coding rule for this study |
| --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |
| Location & Tracking | Permissions that enable location access or location-derived behavioral inference | `ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION`, `ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATION`, `ACCESS_MEDIA_LOCATION` | Can support location-based personalization, nearby content, ads, safety, tracking, and behavioral inference. | Code as high-value because location can become model input for recommendation, ad targeting, risk scoring, and context-aware AI. |
| Camera / Audio / Multimodal AI | Permissions enabling visual/audio input capture or processing | `CAMERA`, `RECORD_AUDIO`, `MEDIA_PROJECTION`, `CAPTURE_VIDEO_OUTPUT` | Relevant to content creation, voice/video features, live streaming, AR effects, computer vision, speech processing, and multimodal AI input. | Code as high-value because these permissions are closest to direct multimodal data capture. |
| Media & Content Access | Permissions enabling access to images, video, audio, or user-generated files | `READ_MEDIA_IMAGES`, `READ_MEDIA_VIDEO`, `READ_MEDIA_AUDIO`, `READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE` | Relevant to user content access, upload flows, content editing, recommendation systems, and multimodal analysis. | Code as high-value because media files can contain rich visual/audio/textual signals. |
| Advertising / Attribution | Permissions linked to ad identifiers, install attribution, custom audiences, topics, or personalization measurement | `AD_ID`, `ACCESS_ADSERVICES_AD_ID`, install referrer permissions | Relevant to ad targeting, measurement, user acquisition analytics, personalization, and monetization. | Code as high-value because ad and attribution permissions connect app behavior to personalization and measurement infrastructure. |
| System Noise | Vendor-specific, launcher, badge, shortcut, push, or internal compatibility permissions | badge/shortcut/vendor permissions, package-specific broadcast permissions | Often inflates raw manifest counts without necessarily implying new user-data access. | Code separately so the study does not confuse compatibility inflation with privacy-sensitive or AI-relevant expansion. |

