### 3.1 Normalized stack groups

| Stack group | Meaning in this study |
| --- | --- |
| High-value / Sensitive / AI-relevant | The core explanatory category: permissions most closely related to AI input, personalization, recommendation, advertising, identity, behavioral monitoring, and sensitive user data access. |
| System / Functional / Background | Functional and system-operation layer: permissions supporting foreground services, background operations, network access, connectivity, and device state. Some growth in this category may reflect Android platform permission-model changes. |
| Commerce / Platform Services | Monetization and platform-service layer: permissions related to billing, install attribution, app-store services, and commercial measurement. |
| Noise / Compatibility / Push | Noise and compatibility layer: launcher badges, vendor push systems, shortcuts, internal package permissions, and device-specific compatibility permissions. This category prevents raw total counts from being misread as direct privacy or AI expansion. |

